thanks to anthony bourdain, but the numerous stalls around the island also offer an equally delightful experience for half the price of ibu oka's. bebek betutu — literally "darkened duck", topped with a herb paste and roasted in banana leaves over charcoal. the same method can also be used for chicken, resulting in ayam betutu. lawar — covers a range of balinese salads, usually involving thinly chopped vegetables, minced meat, coconut and spices. traditionally, blood is mixed into this dish but it is often omitted for the more delicate constitutions of visitors. green beans and chicken are a particularly common 